  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verses 35-38.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - The next morning ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Jonathan went out into the field,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "  not ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "at the time,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " but \"to the place\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "appointed",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", taking with him a ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "little lad,",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " as less likely to suspect a reason. Having shot at the mark, he sends him to pick up the arrows, and as he runs to do so he shoots one beyond him, and, calling aloud, gives David the sign that there was no hope. To keep the boy's attention engaged he gives him hurried commands - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "Make speed, haste, stay not.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " Instead of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "the arrows",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " the written text has \"Jonathan's lad gathered up the arrow,\" ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "i.e.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " that one especially which Jonathan had shot beyond him, and to which his rapid commands referred. 1 Samuel 20:35",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
